## Limitations

The analysis is limited by the availability of up-to-date and comprehensive data on the costs associated with the death penalty. Additionally, the debate over the death penalty is influenced by moral and ethical considerations that extend beyond economic analysis. The findings are based on existing literature and may not capture all nuances of the issue, particularly those related to regional variations in costs and legal processes.

